# Trouvez une commande qui permet de tuer le processus de la commande en background [Commande]
pkill tail

# pkill = processus kill = kills the given processus.
# Alternatively:
# - Use "ps" to get a list of active processes. Find the command (CMD) to kill and its
#   matching PID, then kill it with "kill the-pid" ==> kill 2062
# - Use "jobs" to view the processes active in the background, identify its number,
#   then kill it with "kill %number" ==> kill %1
